                answer: "Mg transfers 2 electrons to O; Mg²⁺ and O²⁻ ions form; both achieve the [Ne] electron configuration. Dot-cross diagram shows [Mg]²⁺ and [::Ö::]²⁻ with square brackets and charges labelled.",
