                group5To6:  "IE drops from Group 5 to Group 6: e.g. N (1402) → O (1314) kJ/mol. Oxygen's 4th 2p electron must pair in an already-occupied orbital, experiencing electron-electron repulsion — this makes it easier to remove than one of nitrogen's singly occupied 2p electrons."
