        evaluate:   "A student states: 'Ionic compounds always conduct electricity because ions carry charge, just like electrons in metals.' Evaluate this statement — identify what is correct, identify the error (specifying the condition that must be met), and explain the correct conditions for ionic conductivity with a mechanistic explanation.",
        create:     "Construct a Born-Haber cycle for the formation of lithium fluoride (LiF) from its elements. Label each enthalpy term (atomisation of Li, atomisation of F, ionisation energy of Li, electron affinity of F, lattice enthalpy, and enthalpy of formation). Use the cycle to explain why LiF has a negative enthalpy of formation despite the positive ionisation energy of Li being a significant energy cost."
