        understand: "Explain why NH₃ has a bond angle of 107° rather than the tetrahedral angle of 109.5°. Your answer must reference the number and type of electron pairs around N and the relative magnitude of their repulsions. Extend your explanation to predict the bond angle in H₂O (104.5°) and explain the further reduction.",
        apply:      "For each of the following molecules: (i) SO₂; (ii) PCl₃; (iii) SF₄; (iv) XeF₂ — use VSEPR theory to predict the number of bonding pairs and lone pairs on the central atom, the molecular shape, and the approximate bond angles. For SO₂, also draw a dot-cross diagram showing the dative bond.",
