        evaluate:   "A student explains metallic conductivity as follows: 'Metals conduct electricity because they have weak bonds that break easily, allowing electrons to escape and flow.' Evaluate every element of this explanation — identify what is correct, identify all errors, and write a complete, accurate account of the mechanism of metallic electrical conduction.",
        create:     "Propose a structural explanation, using the metallic bonding model, for why (a) adding carbon to iron increases hardness (producing steel); (b) an alloy of copper and zinc (brass) is harder than either pure metal; (c) pure gold is too soft for most engineering applications and must be alloyed. Identify the common structural principle in all three cases and connect it to the metallic bonding model."
