        understand: "Explain why the boiling point of H₂O (100°C) is anomalously high compared to H₂S (−60°C), H₂Se (−41°C), and H₂Te (−2°C). Your answer must identify the specific intermolecular force responsible, explain why H₂O can form it while the other Group 16 hydrides cannot, and explain why the trend from H₂S to H₂Te (increasing boiling point) follows the expected pattern.",
        apply:      "For each of the following pairs, predict which substance has the higher boiling point and justify your answer by identifying the intermolecular forces present in each: (a) CH₄ vs NH₃; (b) HCl vs HBr; (c) ethanol (C₂H₅OH) vs dimethyl ether (CH₃OCH₃) — both have Mr = 46.",
