        evaluate:   "A student proposes that 2-chloro-2-methylpropane reacts with NaOH by an SN2 mechanism because 'OH⁻ is a strong nucleophile that can displace any leaving group by back-side attack.' Evaluate this proposal — identify every error; state the correct mechanism for this substrate with justification from substrate class; write the correct mechanism including all steps and intermediates; and explain what 'back-side attack' requires structurally and why it cannot occur here.",
        create:     "Propose a synthetic route to 2-aminopropane starting from propene, in no more than three steps. For each step: write the balanced equation; state the reagents, conditions, and mechanism type; identify major and minor products where applicable. Justify the regiochemistry of the first step using carbocation stability, and explain why excess ammonia is required in the final step."
