        analyze:    "An unknown compound with molecular formula C₄H₈O: gives an orange precipitate with 2,4-DNP; gives no silver mirror with Tollens' reagent; gives no yellow precipitate with I₂/NaOH. A second compound with the same formula gives an orange precipitate with 2,4-DNP; gives a silver mirror with Tollens'; gives no precipitate with I₂/NaOH. Identify both compounds, draw their structural formulae, and explain why the two compounds respond differently to Tollens' reagent by reference to their structural difference at the carbonyl carbon.",
        evaluate:   "Evaluate the following student claim: 'The iodoform test can be used to distinguish ethanal from propanone, because ethanal is an aldehyde and propanone is a ketone — only ketones give a positive iodoform test.' Identify all errors in this statement; state which compounds give a positive iodoform test and why (using structural criteria); and provide a corrected explanation of what the iodoform test actually detects.",
