        understand: "Explain why ethanoyl chloride (CH₃COCl) reacts vigorously with water at room temperature, while ethyl ethanoate (CH₃COOC₂H₅) requires reflux with dilute acid or base to hydrolyse under comparable conditions. Your answer must reference the leaving group ability and the electrophilicity of the carbonyl carbon in each compound.",
