        analyze:    "An unknown compound with molecular formula C₄H₈ is found to: (i) rapidly decolourise bromine water; (ii) show two peaks by ¹H NMR; (iii) exist as two geometric isomers. Deduce the structure, draw both geometric isomers, and explain why the molecular formula C₄H₈ alone is insufficient to identify the compound (state how many structural isomers are consistent with C₄H₈).",
        evaluate:   "Evaluate the claim: 'The major product of HBr addition to propene is 1-bromopropane because, according to Markovnikov's rule, the bromine atom adds to the carbon bearing fewer hydrogen atoms.' Identify every error in this statement — address: (a) which atom adds where; (b) what Markovnikov's rule actually states; (c) which product is actually the major product and why, using carbocation stability as your justification.",
        create:     "Propose a two-step synthetic route to produce 2-bromopropane starting from propane. For each step: state the reagents and conditions; write the balanced equation; draw the mechanism (or state it is free-radical substitution and write all stages); identify any major and minor products. Explain why the two-step route via propene is preferred over direct bromination of propane if high selectivity for 2-bromopropane is required."
